Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for Next.js

## Changes Made:

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics` v1.6.1 to dependencies using pnpm
- Updated `pnpm-lock.yaml` to reflect the new dependency

### 2. Updated Root Layout (app/layout.tsx)
- Imported `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the closing `</ReactLenis>` tag
- Placement ensures proper tracking while maintaining existing layout structure
- Component positioned alongside existing Google Analytics implementation

### 3. Project Structure
- Identified as App Router project (uses `app/` directory)
- Uses pnpm as the package manager
- Root layout file: `app/layout.tsx`

### 4. Testing & Verification
- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ Linting passed with no warnings or errors
- ✅ All unit tests passed (121 tests)
- ✅ No TypeScript compilation errors
- ✅ Lock files properly updated

## Implementation Details:

The Analytics component was strategically placed:
- Inside the `<body>` tag to ensure proper script execution
- After the main application content (ReactLenis wrapper)
- Before the closing `</body>` tag
- Alongside the existing GoogleAnalytics component for comprehensive tracking

This setup ensures Vercel Web Analytics tracks page views and user interactions across the entire application without affecting existing functionality or performance.

## Files Modified:
1. `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
2. `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
